This project is SOURCE-AVAILABLE, NOT OPEN SOURCE (decided 2026-07-11).

The source is published so that the claims the site makes about itself can be
checked against the code that runs it. That is the whole purpose of publication.
It is not a grant of rights to reuse the work.

1. WHAT YOU MAY DO

   You may read, clone, audit, quote, and discuss this source for the purpose of
   verifying what the project does, and for study, commentary, review, security
   research, and journalism.

2. WHAT YOU MAY NOT DO

   Without prior written permission from the copyright holder, you may not copy,
   modify, merge, publish, redistribute, sublicense, or sell this software or
   substantial portions of it, nor deploy it or a derivative of it as a running
   service, product, or token launch.

3. THE MARKS AND THE PLATES ARE EXEMPT — THEY ARE FREE

   The sigil, the five organ glyphs, the kit images, and the plates published by
   the site as "The Marks" carry no rights reservation. The site states of them:
   "No one owns these, including its makers. Take them; the body does not shrink
   from being copied." That declaration governs.

   In this repository those files are:
     web/public/sigil.svg
     web/public/glyphs/
     web/public/kit/

   Take them, use them, alter them, for anything, without attribution or
   permission. To the extent possible in law they are placed in the public domain.

